'''This template is creating working links when translating pages from english to another language.'''

Usage:
<pre>{{en/Manual/Base Set/Link Translation|english page|Language suffix|link text|page1|page2|page3|page4|page5}}</pre>

{{en/Warning|Because "#ifexist:" was somehow broken, this template's check if one of the target pages exists would always return false. Like this: {{#ifexist: Industries | page exists! its working again! | returns false }} }}
* While that check works, the template trys to create links to one of the given (non-english) ''page names''. (Takes up to 5 ''page names'', WITHOUT the "/De", "/Fr" or "/Ru" ... -suffix.)
* If none of the ''page names'' exist, it will give a (dead) link to the first (non-english) ''page1'' AND a Link to the ''english page''.
** The reason why the broken non-english Link is given is that the page can easily be created and is listed at [[:Special:WantedPages]].
** Once one of the Pages has been created, the Template will automatically link there.
* So for a existing link {{en/C|<nowiki>[[en/Example|click this example link]]</nowiki>|}} you would type {{en/C|<nowiki>{{en/Example|</nowiki>''[your language code]''{{en/!}}''[text to display on your link]''{{en/!}}''[Translations for "Example"]''<nowiki>}}</nowiki>|}}

For Example:<pre>{{en/Manual/Base Set/Link Translation|Main Page|De|Siehe auch die Hauptseite|Hauptseite|Main Page}}</pre>will give:
* If one of those exist, a link to "Hauptseite/De" or "Main Page/De" is (probably, see warning above) created, which is displayed with the Text "Siehe auch die Hauptseite".
* If none exist, it will give the first of the upper options, together with the (hopefully working) english link. It will look like this:  {{en/Manual/Base Set/Link Translation|Main Page|De|Siehe auch die Hauptseite|Non-existent-page}}

